      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
         <p>The papers of Charles Burke Elliott (1861-1935) span the years
		  1910-1912 and consist of typewritten diaries, a letterbook, newspaper
		  clippings, and translations from Spanish and Filipino of newspaper articles
		  from the Philippines. The collection focuses exclusively on Elliott’s service
		  in the Philippines as associate justice of the supreme court of the
		  Philippines, 1910-1911, and from 1911 to 1912 as secretary of commerce and
		  police of the second Philippine Commission. The diaries are detailed and
		  extensive, covering social, political, and governmental affairs as well as
		  Elliott’s travels throughout the country and to China. Included are a few
		  memoranda, reports, and copies of letters sent and received relating to
		  conditions in the Philippines and governance of the country, including a
		  memorandum from W. Cameron Forbes on transferring the authority of the office
		  of secretary of commerce and police from him to Elliott.</p>
      </scopecontent>
